.TH "LIGHTNING-TOR" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-tor \- Tor / network privacy for clightning
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning tor
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning tor — Tor / network privacy for clightning.

Implements FEAT-189. Edits lightningd's config in-place to
turn the v3 hidden-service flow on / off, restarts the
daemon (FEAT-183), and verifies the resulting node address.

Subcommands:
  on       enable Tor (proxy + statictor) in lightningd.conf
  off      disable
  status   tor running locally? onion advertised? leak?
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning tor <subcommand>

   on       enable Tor (proxy + v3 hidden service) and restart lightningd
   off      disable Tor
   status   tor running locally?  onion advertised?  clearnet leak?
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
